{
  "stem": "17821.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 322.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I have a letter among the things from this Didier, his name was, that he'd-- for two days, he hadn't got the message.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "When he did get the message, he was a man of influence there, and he came and got us out.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I, I from, me from one camp, Martin from another camp.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I have a photograph among the photographs that I got out there of a little cottage in the hills that he had.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And he put us in his little cottage as long as we needed to stay there.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And Martin went down into town and saw the American attache and sent-- oh, he, Martin, by a miracle-- you like the word miracle again.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Martin had a Hungarian number, an immigration number, which was very unusual because, according to the law that was passed here somewhere in the 1920s, there were only so many they could-- there were a lot of numbers available for British people like me, so to say, because it didn't matter where you, where you were born.",
      "word_count": 57
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But he was born in Hungary.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And by a miracle, he had a number because the British officers had sent him on errands sometimes.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And once he came-- had to come through Paris, and he was walking, suddenly he realized he was walking past the American Embassy.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And he thought, oh, hmm, so he walked in.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And he said, I, I want a number for a visa.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they laughed and they laughed.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "What do you mean?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You, you never, it'd take you I don't know how many years before your number would come up.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Never mind, he said, never mind, give me one just the same.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So he had this number.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
